==English==

===Noun===
''the'' '''[[wee]] [[small]] [[hour]]s''' (''always plural'')

<!-- Ripe for template/category -->
# The [[early]] hours of the morning, just after midnight, when most people are [[asleep]].
#:* He worked into the wee small hours to get everything perfect for the opening day.

====Usage notes====
Within the context of a sentence, almost always used with the definite article "the", especially, or a demonstrative adjetive.

====Synonyms====
*[[oh dark thirty]]
*[[small hours]]
*[[wee hours]]

